Actor Williams Uchemba has stated his mother’s covenant with God resulted in his birth. Much more, Uchemba noted it’s the reason for the many blessings he enjoys. The comic act in his post on Instagram explained that his mother’s desperation for a male child after birthing four girls made her covenant with God to be blessed with one.   Age, grade don’t determine maturity – Regina Daniels     Reality finer than filter – Mercy Johnson     Grateful Cuppy receives dad, sister at Oxford varsity   As such, she vowed to dedicate the child back to God and her prayer was answered as he was born 10 months after. “After 4 girls and in desperate need of a boy my mother told God that if he gives her a son she will dedicate him back to him to serve him, 10 months later I showed up. “So I’m not sorry for being blessed it was a decision that was made in my absence,” the father of one state.